{"componentChunkName":"component---src-template-contents-jsx","path":"/content/mcmcs-optimize/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/content/mcmcs-optimize/"},"html":"<h1>Hill Climbing vs. Gradient Ascent</h1>\n<p><em>This work was performed as part of the 2019 Fall semester, Maths &#x26; Computational Methods for Complex Systems module (817G5) at the University of Sussex. The assignment was programmed in MATLAB, part of the report can be downloaded from here: <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&#x26;id=1prDRPIYDS2IHA34oJX6Y1Wm7lq0MCpCs\">pdf</a></em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>This plot shows the difference between the hill climbing and gradient ascent algorithm in a simple global optimization problem. The optimization landscape is colored based on how many iterations it took for the algorithm to arrive at the maxima (top of the plot).\nLighter colours represents lower number of iterations, while black means did not finish.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style>\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/332ff/mcmcs-optimize.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 45.599999999999994%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source srcset=\"/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/ecc44/mcmcs-optimize.webp 125w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/0e2a5/mcmcs-optimize.webp 250w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/10636/mcmcs-optimize.webp 500w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/db9b4/mcmcs-optimize.webp 750w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/e00f7/mcmcs-optimize.webp 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n        <source srcset=\"/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/57f79/mcmcs-optimize.png 125w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/3e256/mcmcs-optimize.png 250w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/b30f8/mcmcs-optimize.png 500w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/b13e1/mcmcs-optimize.png 750w,\n/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/332ff/mcmcs-optimize.png 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" type=\"image/png\">\n        <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/9c8b2968d289a99f594cfbb6599b8145/b30f8/mcmcs-optimize.png\" alt=\"mcmcs optimize\" title=\"Comparison between hill climbing and gradient ascent. Left is hill climbing, right is gradient ascent.\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\"><p>Comparison between hill climbing and gradient ascent. Left is hill climbing, right is gradient ascent.</p>\n<style class=\"grvsc-styles\">\n  .grvsc-container {\n    overflow: auto;\n    position: relative;\n    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;\n    padding-top: 1rem;\n    padding-top: var(--grvsc-padding-top, var(--grvsc-padding-v, 1rem));\n    padding-bottom: 1rem;\n    padding-bottom: var(--grvsc-padding-bottom, var(--grvsc-padding-v, 1rem));\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    border-radius: var(--grvsc-border-radius, 8px);\n    font-feature-settings: normal;\n    line-height: 1.4;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-code {\n    display: table;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line {\n    display: table-row;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n    width: 100%;\n    position: relative;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line > * {\n    position: relative;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter-pad {\n    display: table-cell;\n    padding-left: 0.75rem;\n    padding-left: calc(var(--grvsc-padding-left, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem)) / 2);\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter {\n    display: table-cell;\n    -webkit-user-select: none;\n    -moz-user-select: none;\n    user-select: none;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter::before {\n    content: attr(data-content);\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-source {\n    display: table-cell;\n    padding-left: 1.5rem;\n    padding-left: var(--grvsc-padding-left, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem));\n    padding-right: 1.5rem;\n    padding-right: var(--grvsc-padding-right, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem));\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-source:empty::after {\n    content: ' ';\n    -webkit-user-select: none;\n    -moz-user-select: none;\n    user-select: none;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter + .grvsc-source {\n    padding-left: 0.75rem;\n    padding-left: calc(var(--grvsc-padding-left, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem)) / 2);\n  }\n  \n  /* Line transformer styles */\n  \n  .grvsc-has-line-highlighting > .grvsc-code > .grvsc-line::before {\n    content: ' ';\n    position: absolute;\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line-diff-add::before {\n    background-color: var(--grvsc-line-diff-add-background-color, rgba(0, 255, 60, 0.2));\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line-diff-del::before {\n    background-color: var(--grvsc-line-diff-del-background-color, rgba(255, 0, 20, 0.2));\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line-number {\n    padding: 0 2px;\n    text-align: right;\n    opacity: 0.7;\n  }\n  \n</style></figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Half of the landscape for gradient ascent algorithm is black, because the algorithm gets trapped in a local minima (the middle ridge). Meanwhile, the hill climbing algorithm is random, which shows in the plot.</p>\n<style class=\"grvsc-styles\">\n  .grvsc-container {\n    overflow: auto;\n    position: relative;\n    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;\n    padding-top: 1rem;\n    padding-top: var(--grvsc-padding-top, var(--grvsc-padding-v, 1rem));\n    padding-bottom: 1rem;\n    padding-bottom: var(--grvsc-padding-bottom, var(--grvsc-padding-v, 1rem));\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    border-radius: var(--grvsc-border-radius, 8px);\